So confused. This place seems to be an Ethiopian  restaurant that started to become a coffee shop and only changed the sings.  It says Ground Up or something to that effect for its business name one the outside advertising organic coffee and a "unique coffee experience." I went in and the place was fully dead.  I asked if they did pour overs and they barista said the did, rung me up and handed me an empty cup.  So generously just a miscommunication but if you are fronting as a posh coffee shop you may obviously choose not to do pour overs but you equally obviously should know what they are.  Whatever, rolled with it. Coffee was tolerable but not good. Went to the seating area. Two spots with outlets next to them.  One was filthy not just crumbs but multiple kinds of sticky covering the whole area.  Went to the next table covered with crumbs but not sticky. I used my coffee cup to push away enough crumbs to sit my stuff down.  Remember, dead.  I was the only one there. Barista socially on the phone when I came in. Outlet turned out to be dead  and spent my minutes there trying to figure out if I had walked into the wrong place before leaving and tossing my coffee a block down.  Shame. Cool shop  that seems trying to do something and maybe great ¿eithopian or gastro pub food? but nothing but potential and lazy barista/owner and blah coffee at the moment hyping itself as something very different.

This place WAS the best I've been to Ethiopian restaurant. But, this is going to be my last time coming here. The men restroom smells bad and it's is noticeable even before you get seated. Once you sat for a minute, you will get used to it. LoL. There are one or two servers that are keen, but I'm assuming they don't work on weekdays. Every time I'm here on weekdays, the servers are slow and sometimes you only see them once when they bring the food. I like the regular kitfo and that was the only reason I come here despite the above issues. The place looks great and not like any other Ethiopian restaurants in the area. The look is different. But, again, if I can't seat or get served, what is the point. Actually, I'm typing this while me and my friend were waiting for one of the servers come get us a bill.
